WEBVTT

1
00:01:12.355 --> 00:01:15.025
Referee, why don't you stop the fight?

2
00:01:22.361 --> 00:01:24.284
Let's go! Let's go!

3
00:01:27.953 --> 00:01:31.250
Come on! Get him!

4
00:01:32.709 --> 00:01:34.921
Come on! Hit him! Hit him!

5
00:01:58.403 --> 00:02:01.406
You're waltzing.
Give the sucker some action.

6
00:02:01.989 --> 00:02:04.909
You're fighting like a bum.
Want some advice?

7
00:02:04.992 --> 00:02:06.075
Water.

8
00:02:06.159 --> 00:02:08.078
Cold beer here!

9
00:02:09.914 --> 00:02:12.750
Should I bet the fight don't go
three rounds? You feel strong?

10
00:02:12.834 --> 00:02:15.252
- Absolutely.
- Cold beer!

11
00:02:15.336 --> 00:02:18.256
- You want some good advice?
- Mouthpiece.

12
00:02:29.473 --> 00:02:31.019
Come on, Rock!

13
00:03:39.961 --> 00:03:42.131
All right. All right.

14
00:03:42.548 --> 00:03:47.133
Next a six-rounder
between local lightweights Kid Brooks

15
00:03:47.300 --> 00:03:49.013
and Sugar Johnson.

16
00:03:57.187 --> 00:03:58.895
Good going, champ.

17
00:04:00.650 --> 00:04:02.318
- Hey.
- Say what?

18
00:04:02.401 --> 00:04:05.485
- You got a smoke?
- Yeah, you can have this one.

19
00:04:06.406 --> 00:04:07.907
You're a bum.

20
00:04:08.324 --> 00:04:11.157
You're a bum, you know that?
You're a bum!

21
00:04:39.939 --> 00:04:42.064
You really got lucky tonight.

22
00:04:42.149 --> 00:04:43.692
Spider, here's loser's share.

23
00:04:43.776 --> 00:04:46.362
$40, less $15 locker and cornerman,

24
00:04:46.446 --> 00:04:49.281
$5 shower and towel, 7 percent tax.

25
00:04:49.365 --> 00:04:51.367
Comes to 17.20.

26
00:04:51.451 --> 00:04:53.870
You fought a good fight, Spider.

27
00:04:53.951 --> 00:04:56.247
Balboa, you get winner's share, $65.

28
00:04:56.329 --> 00:05:01.209
Less $15 locker and cornerman,
$5 shower and towel and 7 percent tax.

29
00:05:01.293 --> 00:05:03.754
Comes to 40.55.

30
00:05:04.713 --> 00:05:07.507
- When do I fight again?
- Maybe two weeks.

31
00:05:07.716 --> 00:05:11.471
Give me a call. The doctor should be in
in about 20 minutes.

32
00:05:47.838 --> 00:05:49.425
Hey, boy.

33
00:06:44.980 --> 00:06:47.733
You guys are getting better every year.
You know that?

34
00:06:48.358 --> 00:06:49.485
Yeah.

35
00:08:01.557 --> 00:08:04.560
Hey, your old man did pretty good tonight.

36
00:08:04.644 --> 00:08:06.478
Why weren't you there?

37
00:08:06.562 --> 00:08:09.273
You should've seen me. You guys hungry?

38
00:08:11.733 --> 00:08:13.194
Here you go.

39
00:08:14.403 --> 00:08:15.778
Here you go.

40
00:08:18.324 --> 00:08:21.076
You wanna see
your friend Moby Dick, huh?

41
00:08:24.372 --> 00:08:27.290
How you doing, Moby Dick?
You miss me today?

42
00:08:31.086 --> 00:08:32.588
Here you go. Say hi.

43
00:08:32.672 --> 00:08:36.341
If you guys could sing or dance,
I wouldn't be doing this.

44
00:08:53.274 --> 00:08:56.528
And this turtle food I got here, it's...

45
00:08:57.903 --> 00:08:59.907
This turtle food I got here
has more flies in it...

46
00:08:59.990 --> 00:09:01.868
There are more moths in it than flies.

47
00:09:01.951 --> 00:09:05.120
More flies... More moths...
Who the hell cares?

48
00:10:25.908 --> 00:10:28.576
How you feeling this morning? Full of life?

49
00:10:28.663 --> 00:10:30.038
Fine.

50
00:10:30.123 --> 00:10:32.041
How you doing, killer?

51
00:10:32.375 --> 00:10:35.086
- How's the turtle food this week?
- Fine.

52
00:10:36.043 --> 00:10:37.839
I'm kind of aggravated.

53
00:10:37.922 --> 00:10:39.129
Oh, I'm sorry.

54
00:10:39.215 --> 00:10:41.841
Ain't your fault.
You don't wanna hear about it?

55
00:10:41.926 --> 00:10:43.720
I'll tell you somebody
who don't wanna hear about it.

56
00:10:43.802 --> 00:10:45.763
- How you doing, Gloria?
- Good.

57
00:10:45.846 --> 00:10:50.018
The last turtle food I got here
had more moths in it than flies, Adrian.

58
00:10:50.100 --> 00:10:51.894
These moths get caught
in the turtle's throat

59
00:10:51.975 --> 00:10:54.937
and they cough, and I gotta smack them
on the back of the shell

60
00:10:55.023 --> 00:10:56.899
and what do you think they get?

61
00:10:56.980 --> 00:10:58.524
They get what?

62
00:11:00.778 --> 00:11:02.864
Come on. Shell shock.

63
00:11:03.403 --> 00:11:04.907
They get shell-shocked.
What do you think?

64
00:11:04.990 --> 00:11:07.076
You're starting with
the bad jokes early, huh?

65
00:11:07.158 --> 00:11:09.701
Well, no.
Inventing jokes ain't so easy sometimes.

66
00:11:09.787 --> 00:11:11.663
No, that wasn't no joke.

67
00:11:11.748 --> 00:11:14.875
Hey, how's my buddy doing today?
Yo, Butkus.

68
00:11:14.956 --> 00:11:16.586
Yo, Butkus!

69
00:11:17.668 --> 00:11:19.047
What is it?

70
00:11:22.759 --> 00:11:25.219
Hey, give me a kiss.

71
00:11:25.302 --> 00:11:29.389
Adrian, go downstairs and clean
all the cat cages. They're a mess.

72
00:11:43.696 --> 00:11:46.532
You gotta pay for that turtle food,
rock head.

73
00:11:46.947 --> 00:11:49.869
Hey, crime don't pay.
You know that, Gloria.

74
00:12:14.432 --> 00:12:16.812
- Yo, Rock, how's your boss?
- Real good.

75
00:12:16.894 --> 00:12:18.855
Hey, Rock, you fighting again?

76
00:12:18.940 --> 00:12:20.899
- Here and there.
- We'll make some money real soon, huh?

77
00:12:20.980 --> 00:12:22.942
Yeah, a million dollars.

78
00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:25.778
Hey, you. Where are you going?

79
00:12:31.119 --> 00:12:33.870
Where are you going? Where you running?

80
00:12:34.413 --> 00:12:36.456
- Where you running?
- Hey! Hey!

81
00:12:36.541 --> 00:12:39.125
- Hey! Don't hit the face!
- Shut up!

82
00:12:39.210 --> 00:12:41.504
- Not the face!
- Mr. Gazzo wants the 200 now.

83
00:12:41.586 --> 00:12:42.797
I'm broke!

84
00:12:42.879 --> 00:12:46.048
Mr. Gazzo says I should get the 200
or break your thumb. You understand?

85
00:12:46.134 --> 00:12:48.970
- Please, don't...
- What's your name again?

86
00:12:49.802 --> 00:12:52.807
- Bob!
- Bob. Listen, Bob.

87
00:12:53.850 --> 00:12:56.519
You wanna dance, you gotta pay the band.
You understand?

88
00:12:56.600 --> 00:12:58.855
You wanna borrow,
you gotta pay the man.

89
00:12:58.937 --> 00:13:02.316
Hey, I ain't emotionally involved, Bob.
You understand?

90
00:13:02.399 --> 00:13:05.028
Give me some money.
Give me some money.

91
00:13:09.615 --> 00:13:11.240
There's 130 here.

92
00:13:11.325 --> 00:13:13.283
That's it. I'm broke.

93
00:13:13.369 --> 00:13:16.788
Hey, Bob, you're still $70 light.

94
00:13:17.288 --> 00:13:20.206
You don't have to break nothing.
Take my coat.

95
00:13:20.293 --> 00:13:22.336
It's worth $50, $60.

96
00:13:22.793 --> 00:13:24.464
Take the coat!

97
00:13:26.048 --> 00:13:27.548
You know, you should've planned ahead.

98
00:13:27.633 --> 00:13:29.759
You know that?
You should've planned ahead.

99
00:13:29.844 --> 00:13:32.177
We'll fake it. I'll tape up the hand
like you broke the thumb!

100
00:13:32.263 --> 00:13:34.849
- Should've planned ahead.
- Gazzo don't have to know!

101
00:13:34.932 --> 00:13:37.975
He won't be wise to nothing!
Gazzo won't be wise to nothing!

102
00:13:38.061 --> 00:13:40.855
Keep the coat! Keep the...

103
00:14:09.884 --> 00:14:14.013
He only had 130, but I think he's good
for the rest next week, Mr. Gazzo.

104
00:14:14.096 --> 00:14:16.389
Sure, Rocky. Bob's good for it.

105
00:14:17.642 --> 00:14:19.432
That's it for today.

106
00:14:20.519 --> 00:14:23.815
Tomorrow collect from Del Rio.
He's late three weeks. I don't like it.

107
00:14:23.898 --> 00:14:26.234
Tomorrow, three weeks. Del Rio?

108
00:14:26.649 --> 00:14:28.860
All right, I got it.
How do you spell Del Rio?

109
00:14:28.945 --> 00:14:31.239
- How'd you do last night?
- I did real good.

110
00:14:31.322 --> 00:14:32.740
- Hey.
- What?

111
00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:35.658
- Did you get the license number?
- Of what?

112
00:14:35.743 --> 00:14:37.576
The truck that run over your face.

113
00:14:37.662 --> 00:14:39.745
Relax, Buddy. Pull it over here.

114
00:14:39.831 --> 00:14:43.292
I wanna let Rocky out.
I'm gonna talk to him for a few seconds.

115
00:15:06.105 --> 00:15:08.024
Why didn't you break this guy's thumb?

116
00:15:08.109 --> 00:15:10.403
- How do you know I didn't?
- You don't think I hear things?

117
00:15:10.485 --> 00:15:12.278
Didn't I give you a job this morning?

118
00:15:12.363 --> 00:15:15.240
- Yeah.
- Why didn't you break his thumb?

119
00:15:15.322 --> 00:15:19.162
When you don't do what I tell you to do,
you make me look bad.

120
00:15:19.326 --> 00:15:22.288
I figured... Look.
I figured if I break the guy's thumb,

121
00:15:22.373 --> 00:15:23.706
he gets laid off.

122
00:15:23.791 --> 00:15:26.668
- He can't make money.
- Let me do the figuring.

123
00:15:26.753 --> 00:15:29.129
From here on in, let me do the figuring.

124
00:15:29.211 --> 00:15:33.259
These guys think we're running a charity,
they'll get off light.

125
00:15:33.341 --> 00:15:35.845
From here on in, do what I tell you to do,

126
00:15:35.927 --> 00:15:37.427
because it's bad for my reputation.

127
00:15:37.513 --> 00:15:40.264
You understand? You got it, Rock?

128
00:15:41.307 --> 00:15:42.600
I got it.

129
00:15:45.437 --> 00:15:47.480
How do you spell Del Rio?

130
00:15:47.815 --> 00:15:50.317
- Look it up in a dictionary.
- Come on!

131
00:15:50.399 --> 00:15:53.571
I won't let that happen no more,
about the thumb.

132
00:15:55.447 --> 00:15:56.740
You know?

133
00:15:57.865 --> 00:15:59.576
So long, meat bag.

134
00:16:02.413 --> 00:16:04.666
I should've broke your thumbs!

135
00:16:34.360 --> 00:16:36.489
Hey, Rock. Heard you did good last night.

136
00:16:36.572 --> 00:16:39.615
- Absolutely. Should've seen me.
- Shouldn't you take a rest?

137
00:16:39.701 --> 00:16:41.576
- No, my back is hurt.
- Your back?

138
00:16:41.658 --> 00:16:43.745
My back is hurt. You deaf?

139
00:16:43.830 --> 00:16:45.373
No, I'm short.

140
00:17:49.979 --> 00:17:51.519
Hey, yo, Mike.

141
00:17:51.894 --> 00:17:54.567
Where's my lock?
Whose stuff is this in my locker?

142
00:17:54.650 --> 00:17:57.862
It's Dipper's stuff.
It ain't your locker no more.

143
00:18:00.403 --> 00:18:03.115
What you talking about?
It's been my locker for six years.

144
00:18:03.201 --> 00:18:04.576
Where's my gear?

145
00:18:04.661 --> 00:18:07.288
Mickey told me to bag it and hang it.

146
00:18:11.914 --> 00:18:14.125
You put my stuff on skid row.

147
00:18:14.211 --> 00:18:18.298
I been in that locker for six years,
and you put my stuff on skid row?

148
00:18:18.383 --> 00:18:20.798
Mickey tells me what to do, I gotta do it.

149
00:18:20.884 --> 00:18:22.303
Where is he?

150
00:18:22.384 --> 00:18:24.806
He's outside working with Dipper.

151
00:18:25.010 --> 00:18:27.266
- He's in a bad mood.
- So am I.

152
00:18:37.652 --> 00:18:39.153
Keep your hands up.

153
00:18:39.237 --> 00:18:41.989
Keep your hands up. Watch the right.

154
00:18:42.403 --> 00:18:43.740
- Hey, Mick.
- Shut up!

155
00:18:43.825 --> 00:18:45.990
To the body. Attaboy.

156
00:18:49.122 --> 00:18:51.124
Time. Time!

157
00:18:53.084 --> 00:18:54.750
What do you want?

158
00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:57.171
- How you feeling today?
- What?

159
00:18:57.255 --> 00:18:59.336
- How you feeling?
- Are you a doctor?

160
00:18:59.423 --> 00:19:02.384
- You have problems today?
- Never mind. What's your problem?

161
00:19:02.468 --> 00:19:06.471
I been talking to Michael.
How come I been put out of my locker?

162
00:19:06.556 --> 00:19:09.932
Because Dipper needed it.
Dipper's a contender.

163
00:19:10.018 --> 00:19:12.225
He's a climber.
Do you know what you are?

164
00:19:12.309 --> 00:19:14.605
- You're a tomato.
- Tomato?

165
00:19:14.689 --> 00:19:17.855
I run a business here,
not a goddamn soup kitchen.

166
00:19:17.942 --> 00:19:19.902
- Did you fight last night?
- Yeah.

167
00:19:19.986 --> 00:19:22.986
- Did you win?
- Yeah, I won K.O. In the second.

168
00:19:23.070 --> 00:19:24.778
Yeah? Who'd you fight?

169
00:19:24.865 --> 00:19:26.284
Spider Rico.

170
00:19:26.615 --> 00:19:28.036
He's a bum!

171
00:19:28.741 --> 00:19:32.202
- You think everybody I fight is a bum.
- Well, ain't they?

172
00:19:32.288 --> 00:19:35.414
You got heart,
but you fight like a goddamn ape.

173
00:19:35.789 --> 00:19:38.711
The only thing special about you,
you never got your nose busted.

174
00:19:38.796 --> 00:19:42.508
Leave it that way. Nice and pretty
and what's left of your mind.

175
00:19:42.592 --> 00:19:45.303
I think I'm gonna go take a steam.
You know why?

176
00:19:45.384 --> 00:19:48.054
Because I did good last night,
and you should've seen me.

177
00:19:48.137 --> 00:19:50.682
- Big deal.
- You should've seen me too.

178
00:19:50.767 --> 00:19:52.057
Hey, kid.

179
00:19:52.477 --> 00:19:54.979
- You ever think about retiring?
- No.

180
00:19:55.063 --> 00:19:56.730
- You think about it.
- Yeah.

181
00:19:56.814 --> 00:19:58.395
All right, time.

182
00:19:58.480 --> 00:20:00.067
- Time!
- What?

183
00:20:00.356 --> 00:20:02.278
I dig your locker, man.

184
00:20:05.073 --> 00:20:06.740
Dig your locker.

185
00:20:09.115 --> 00:20:10.240
Attaboy.

186
00:20:40.942 --> 00:20:42.356
Cold night.

187
00:20:43.317 --> 00:20:46.364
Whew! Good night to catch pneumonia,
you know?

188
00:20:50.115 --> 00:20:52.116
You need some help?

189
00:20:52.951 --> 00:20:55.873
There's a good game
at the Spectrum tonight.

190
00:20:58.375 --> 00:21:00.836
You wanna go to a basketball game?

191
00:21:03.961 --> 00:21:05.758
Hi, Butkus. Hi, kid.

192
00:21:08.720 --> 00:21:11.305
Tough day today.
They took my locker away.

193
00:21:11.385 --> 00:21:14.182
I had that locker for six years.
It don't bother me.

194
00:21:14.267 --> 00:21:15.807
Lockers are bad, anyway, after a while.

195
00:21:15.893 --> 00:21:17.144
People get the combination.

196
00:21:17.228 --> 00:21:21.105
I must've had 20 bucks
taken out of there in the past 6 years.

197
00:21:21.395 --> 00:21:24.231
Don't sound like much, but it adds up.

198
00:21:24.317 --> 00:21:26.362
Doesn't matter. Who cares?

199
00:21:28.278 --> 00:21:30.573
Yeah, cold night. Hey, birds.

200
00:21:30.656 --> 00:21:33.326
Hey, look who's here. Look who's here.

201
00:21:33.411 --> 00:21:34.951
The giant worm.

202
00:21:36.163 --> 00:21:40.375
Look at these birds.
Don't these birds look like flying candy?

203
00:21:40.460 --> 00:21:42.293
Bird, you wanna fly me home?

204
00:21:42.376 --> 00:21:44.881
You need somebody to walk you home?

205
00:21:45.131 --> 00:21:46.298
- No.
- No?

206
00:21:47.048 --> 00:21:50.928
It's a cold night.
If you got the money, take a cab.

207
00:21:51.009 --> 00:21:53.135
Too many creeps around here.

208
00:21:53.765 --> 00:21:56.307
Every other block, there's a creep.

209
00:21:56.642 --> 00:21:58.807
You can always tell a creep.

210
00:22:00.894 --> 00:22:02.690
Listen. I'm gonna go now, okay?

211
00:22:02.770 --> 00:22:04.480
I'll see you later, all right?

212
00:22:04.567 --> 00:22:08.359
None of you guys get up.
I know you had a hard day in the cage.

213
00:22:08.443 --> 00:22:09.653
So,

214
00:22:09.903 --> 00:22:12.659
I'm gonna go home, make up a joke.
I'll tell you a new joke tomorrow.

215
00:22:12.740 --> 00:22:14.490
Okay? Good night, Adrian.

216
00:22:14.576 --> 00:22:16.287
Good night, Rocky.

217
00:22:35.346 --> 00:22:37.392
Don't know what happened.

218
00:22:38.643 --> 00:22:41.558
Hey, there, Lefty. Got a friend for you here.

219
00:22:41.644 --> 00:22:43.855
- Hello, Rock.
- How you doing?

220
00:22:43.940 --> 00:22:46.150
- You seen Paulie?
- Yeah, he's in the steam room.

221
00:22:46.230 --> 00:22:49.067
- Yeah.
- Hey, Rocky. What's with the eye?

222
00:22:49.153 --> 00:22:51.112
- Been fighting.
- Hope you won it, at least.

223
00:22:51.195 --> 00:22:53.028
Oh, yeah, did real good.
You should've seen me.

224
00:22:53.115 --> 00:22:56.076
<i>... heavyweight champion of the world</i>
<i>Apollo Creed at Kennedy Airport...</i>

225
00:22:56.160 --> 00:22:58.287
Hey, Rock, who'd you fight?

226
00:22:58.371 --> 00:22:59.788
Spider Rico.

227
00:23:00.163 --> 00:23:02.125
Jesus. Is he still around?

228
00:23:02.208 --> 00:23:05.375
Yeah, he's doing real good.
He's doing better than you are.

229
00:23:05.461 --> 00:23:09.086
Hey, Paulie. What, do you lock the door?
Yo, Paulie.

230
00:23:09.837 --> 00:23:12.215
I'd like to kill the freaking moron
who broke the mirror.

231
00:23:12.298 --> 00:23:13.928
Hey, yo, Paulie.

232
00:23:14.634 --> 00:23:19.057
Every day, every night, I pass by.
Your sister's giving me the shoulder.

233
00:23:19.142 --> 00:23:20.807
- Forget her.
- What do you mean?

234
00:23:20.893 --> 00:23:22.894
- You can do better than her.
- I don't forget nothing.

235
00:23:22.979 --> 00:23:25.019
Every night I pass by, I tell a joke.

236
00:23:25.105 --> 00:23:27.730
Every morning I pass by, I tell a joke.

237
00:23:27.817 --> 00:23:29.902
She just looks at me,
you know what I mean?

238
00:23:29.986 --> 00:23:32.903
- Looks?
- Yeah, like I'm a plate of leftovers.

239
00:23:32.989 --> 00:23:34.740
I need a Cadillac
to connect with your sister?

240
00:23:34.824 --> 00:23:37.076
Something wrong with my face?

241
00:23:37.826 --> 00:23:39.745
She's a freaking loser.

242
00:23:39.828 --> 00:23:43.082
Sometimes she gets me so crazy,
I could split her head with a razor.

243
00:23:43.163 --> 00:23:46.085
- Don't get mental.
- You caught me in a bad mood.

