I want you out of the kitchen right now.

480
00:35:56.606 --> 00:35:57.858
I won't.

481
00:36:02.739 --> 00:36:05.282
I want you out of here instamatically!

482
00:36:05.364 --> 00:36:07.994
I'm sick of seeing you
hanging around like a freaking spider.

483
00:36:08.077 --> 00:36:10.246
Go out and live. Enjoy life!

484
00:36:10.454 --> 00:36:12.081
I can't go!

485
00:36:12.164 --> 00:36:14.083
Don't get wise with me now.

486
00:36:14.166 --> 00:36:15.876
I'm tired of you being a loser.

487
00:36:15.960 --> 00:36:18.128
Don't call me that, Paulie!

488
00:36:18.210 --> 00:36:21.132
<i>Apollo Creed says he'll be shopping</i>
<i>for another victim</i>

489
00:36:21.215 --> 00:36:24.969
<i>to fill Green's vacancy</i>
<i>for the Bicentennial championship fight...</i>

490
00:36:25.052 --> 00:36:26.762
Why didn't you tell me
you were bringing him home?

491
00:36:26.846 --> 00:36:28.139
How do you know I didn't?

492
00:36:28.222 --> 00:36:31.059
I can't go, Paulie. I won't go!

493
00:36:31.141 --> 00:36:32.226
Why?

494
00:36:33.226 --> 00:36:36.688
Paulie, it's Thanksgiving.
I got a turkey in the oven.

495
00:36:37.398 --> 00:36:39.442
Oh, a turkey in the oven.

496
00:36:46.157 --> 00:36:47.909
Turkey in the oven.

497
00:36:54.998 --> 00:36:58.710
You want the bird?
Go in the alley and eat the bird!

498
00:36:59.335 --> 00:37:00.797
Aw, Paulie!

499
00:37:01.797 --> 00:37:04.759
I want you out of here!
Get out of the house!

500
00:37:05.009 --> 00:37:07.552
Go out and enjoy your freaking life!

501
00:37:11.766 --> 00:37:13.434
You hungry, Rock?

502
00:37:20.108 --> 00:37:23.820
Hey, yo, Paulie, maybe we better
forget all this, you know?

503
00:37:24.320 --> 00:37:27.447
Forget nothing. Go ahead.
Tell her something funny.

504
00:37:27.532 --> 00:37:30.702
Ain't nothing to talk about.
She's in a bad mood. I'm in a bad mood.

505
00:37:30.784 --> 00:37:33.538
You can do funny things.
You wanna go out with my sister?

506
00:37:33.621 --> 00:37:35.164
- Yeah.
- Well...

507
00:37:39.376 --> 00:37:41.003
I don't know what to say.

508
00:37:41.085 --> 00:37:42.255
Funny.

509
00:37:53.891 --> 00:37:56.018
Yo, Adrian. It's me, Rocky.

510
00:37:56.393 --> 00:37:58.061
Rocky, you know?

511
00:37:58.730 --> 00:37:59.938
Listen,

512
00:38:02.233 --> 00:38:06.695
I don't know what to say, 'cause I ain't
never talked to no door before.

513
00:38:07.864 --> 00:38:11.074
What do I say to a door?
We better forget this.

514
00:38:11.409 --> 00:38:12.577
You're doing fine.

515
00:38:12.659 --> 00:38:14.996
I ain't doing fine. I look like an idiot.

516
00:38:15.079 --> 00:38:17.081
Keep doing what you're doing. Funny.

517
00:38:17.164 --> 00:38:19.375
I know all about these things.

518
00:38:19.458 --> 00:38:21.210
I feel like a jerk.

519
00:38:27.215 --> 00:38:29.635
Yo, Adrian, it's Rocky again.

520
00:38:29.719 --> 00:38:34.306
Listen, I know you ain't too happy
at this moment.

521
00:38:34.849 --> 00:38:36.516
But could you do me a favor?

522
00:38:36.601 --> 00:38:39.603
I ain't got nobody
to spend Thanksgiving with.

523
00:38:39.771 --> 00:38:43.106
So, how about maybe you and I

524
00:38:43.190 --> 00:38:44.983
go out together, get something to eat.

525
00:38:45.068 --> 00:38:47.612
Maybe laugh a little bit.
Who knows, you know?

526
00:38:47.695 --> 00:38:49.447
Would you like to...

527
00:38:51.282 --> 00:38:54.117
Would you like to, maybe,
you and me go out together?

528
00:38:54.202 --> 00:38:56.788
What do you think? Would you like to?

529
00:39:01.793 --> 00:39:04.003
We're gonna have a good time.

530
00:39:04.378 --> 00:39:06.547
We'll have a real good time.

531
00:39:11.094 --> 00:39:12.887
Thanks for the bird.

532
00:39:16.516 --> 00:39:19.434
I'm gonna turn the TV off.
I got a headache.

533
00:39:31.780 --> 00:39:34.199
- What's your sister like to do?
- Ice-skate.

534
00:39:34.282 --> 00:39:36.284
Adrian, come on.
You're letting the heat out.

535
00:39:36.369 --> 00:39:38.663
Who pays the bills around here?

536
00:39:44.251 --> 00:39:47.380
Listen, I don't want no turkey anyway,
you know?

537
00:39:48.965 --> 00:39:50.967
But it was Thanksgiving.

538
00:39:51.800 --> 00:39:52.927
What?

539
00:39:53.010 --> 00:39:54.971
- It was Thanksgiving.
- Yeah, to you.

540
00:39:55.054 --> 00:39:57.347
But to me it's Thursday, right?

541
00:40:21.706 --> 00:40:24.375
- It looks kind of quiet.
- I think it's closed.

542
00:40:24.458 --> 00:40:27.585
No, I think we're just early
or something like that.

543
00:40:29.005 --> 00:40:30.840
- We're closed.
- What?

544
00:40:31.172 --> 00:40:34.135
- I said we're closed.
- Yeah. Hey, listen.

545
00:40:34.217 --> 00:40:37.554
I'm gonna smooth this guy out. Wait here.
I'll be right back.

546
00:40:37.764 --> 00:40:39.556
- We could go someplace else.
- No, it's okay.

547
00:40:39.639 --> 00:40:43.603
Are you closed to the general public,
or are you just closed to everybody?

548
00:40:43.686 --> 00:40:47.856
It's after 6:00. It's Thanksgiving.
That's why there's nobody here.

549
00:40:48.190 --> 00:40:50.233
Besides, you ain't supposed to be in here.

550
00:40:50.318 --> 00:40:52.820
So do me a favor and not stay here.

551
00:40:52.902 --> 00:40:56.449
- Could you do me a favor?
- Come on. We're not operating.

552
00:40:56.699 --> 00:40:59.534
Look. This girl here ain't feeling well.

553
00:40:59.619 --> 00:41:02.163
Doctors say she should go out
and exercise.

554
00:41:02.246 --> 00:41:04.373
Ice-skating's probably the best thing.

555
00:41:04.456 --> 00:41:05.708
So what do you want from me?

556
00:41:05.791 --> 00:41:07.668
Well, hey, I want you to do me a favor.

557
00:41:07.751 --> 00:41:09.335
You can see she ain't feeling too good.

558
00:41:09.420 --> 00:41:12.422
If you can let her on the ice
for a few minutes, I'd appreciate it.

559
00:41:12.507 --> 00:41:14.300
Ten minutes, ten bucks.

560
00:41:14.384 --> 00:41:16.552
Ten bucks? How about eight bucks?

561
00:41:16.635 --> 00:41:18.762
Come on. It's Thanksgiving.

562
00:41:19.012 --> 00:41:20.889
All right. Nine bucks, you got a deal.

563
00:41:20.972 --> 00:41:23.726
You have the ice to yourself. Ten bucks.

564
00:41:25.853 --> 00:41:27.605
Give her the blades.

565
00:41:28.398 --> 00:41:29.690
Aren't you skating?

566
00:41:29.773 --> 00:41:31.733
No, I ain't skated since I was 15.

567
00:41:31.818 --> 00:41:34.112
That's when I started fighting.

568
00:41:34.402 --> 00:41:37.072
Skating's kind of bad for the ankles,
you know?

569
00:41:38.032 --> 00:41:40.784
You're a pretty good skater, aren't you?

570
00:41:41.577 --> 00:41:44.079
Like I was saying
before on the way over here,

571
00:41:44.163 --> 00:41:47.333
fighting used to be tops with me,
but no more.

572
00:41:47.416 --> 00:41:49.918
All I wanted to do out of fighting
was prove I was no bum,

573
00:41:50.003 --> 00:41:52.422
that I had the stuff to make a good pro.

574
00:41:52.505 --> 00:41:55.507
- You never got the chance?
- I ain't crying about it.

575
00:41:55.590 --> 00:41:57.844
I still fight. I do it like a hobby.

576
00:41:57.927 --> 00:42:00.096
The trouble is I'm a southpaw.

577
00:42:00.179 --> 00:42:03.099
- What's a southpaw?
- A southpaw means you're left-handed.

578
00:42:03.181 --> 00:42:05.559
A southpaw throws your timing off.

579
00:42:05.643 --> 00:42:07.936
It throws other guys' timing off,
makes them look awkward.

580
00:42:08.021 --> 00:42:09.605
Nobody wants to look awkward.

581
00:42:09.688 --> 00:42:12.858
- You know where "southpaw" came from?
- Nine minutes!

582
00:42:12.942 --> 00:42:15.987
A long time ago, there was this guy,
maybe a couple hundred years ago,

583
00:42:16.070 --> 00:42:19.532
he was fighting in the...
I think it was around Philadelphia.

584
00:42:19.614 --> 00:42:23.577
His arm... He was left-handed.
His arm was facing towards New Jersey.

585
00:42:23.661 --> 00:42:27.498
And that's south. So naturally
they called him "south paw." You see?

586
00:42:27.581 --> 00:42:30.876
Southpaw, South Jersey, South Camden.

587
00:42:31.335 --> 00:42:33.170
Southpaw. You know what I mean?

588
00:42:34.672 --> 00:42:36.797
Things probably worked out for the best,
don't you think?

589
00:42:36.882 --> 00:42:39.552
Never got a chance
because you're left-handed, huh?

590
00:42:39.635 --> 00:42:41.721
That's absolutely true, you know?

591
00:42:41.804 --> 00:42:43.056
Watch out.

592
00:42:45.056 --> 00:42:48.101
Ah! Ah! I just dislocated my finger.

593
00:42:48.436 --> 00:42:49.978
Ah! Look at that.

594
00:42:50.730 --> 00:42:52.523
Wait. It ain't your fault. Look.

595
00:42:52.606 --> 00:42:54.983
See? I had it... It's an old wound.

596
00:42:55.068 --> 00:42:57.320
You see that? Look. See?

597
00:42:57.402 --> 00:42:58.820
Nothing. It bends like that.

598
00:42:58.905 --> 00:43:01.864
I originally done it... Push the button.
Bong. It works.

599
00:43:01.949 --> 00:43:04.827
- It ain't your fault. Look.
- Seven minutes!

600
00:43:05.577 --> 00:43:08.581
I originally done it...
I carry pictures of all my fights.

601
00:43:08.664 --> 00:43:11.416
I originally done it
in the Baby Crenshaw fight.

602
00:43:11.501 --> 00:43:14.545
Baby's about the size of an airplane.
I broke both hands on his face.

603
00:43:14.628 --> 00:43:18.007
I lost that fight, but that's a nice picture,
don't you think?

604
00:43:18.090 --> 00:43:19.425
Real nice.

605
00:43:20.885 --> 00:43:23.262
Come on. You having a good time?

606
00:43:23.971 --> 00:43:25.889
You can see I ain't too graceful.

607
00:43:25.972 --> 00:43:30.353
I don't move well, but I can really swat.
I can really hit hard.

608
00:43:30.436 --> 00:43:34.106
But I'm a southpaw,
and nobody wants to fight no southpaw.

609
00:43:39.320 --> 00:43:42.072
You know how I got started in fighting?

610
00:43:42.155 --> 00:43:43.239
No.

611
00:43:44.032 --> 00:43:45.952
Am I talking too loud?

612
00:43:46.244 --> 00:43:47.829
Three minutes!

613
00:43:47.911 --> 00:43:52.458
My father, he's a...
My old man, he was never too smart.

614
00:43:52.541 --> 00:43:54.626
He says to me,
"You weren't born with much of a brain,

615
00:43:54.710 --> 00:43:57.213
"so you better start using your body."

616
00:43:57.295 --> 00:43:59.215
So I become a fighter.

617
00:43:59.882 --> 00:44:01.634
You know what I mean?

618
00:44:01.717 --> 00:44:03.552
Why you laughing?

619
00:44:04.887 --> 00:44:07.806
My mother, she said the opposite thing.

620
00:44:07.889 --> 00:44:10.143
What did she say the opposite?

621
00:44:10.768 --> 00:44:13.061
She said,
"You weren't born with much of a body,

622
00:44:13.146 --> 00:44:14.896
"so you better develop your brain."

623
00:44:14.981 --> 00:44:17.733
- Did she say that?
- Yo, time!

624
00:44:19.027 --> 00:44:21.902
- Can I ask you a question?
- Absolutely.

625
00:44:23.155 --> 00:44:26.576
- Why do you wanna fight?
- 'Cause I can't sing or dance.

626
00:44:28.244 --> 00:44:29.954
Don't fall!

627
00:44:31.204 --> 00:44:33.623
That was terrific. I'm pretty good at this.

628
00:44:33.708 --> 00:44:34.958
You like the way I skate?

629
00:44:35.043 --> 00:44:38.085
Last fight I had,
I had with this guy named Spider Rico.

630
00:44:38.170 --> 00:44:40.882
He busted my head up there.
You see that scar?

631
00:44:40.965 --> 00:44:43.967
I'll tell you,
things get pretty rough in the ring.

632
00:44:53.436 --> 00:44:56.396
You know,
some people are very shy by nature.

633
00:44:57.315 --> 00:44:58.690
I suppose.

634
00:45:01.610 --> 00:45:04.489
I say you're very shy by nature, you know?

635
00:45:05.739 --> 00:45:07.114
I suppose.

636
00:45:09.786 --> 00:45:11.536
The bum from the dark.

637
00:45:11.621 --> 00:45:13.289
Get a job, you bum!

638
00:45:14.123 --> 00:45:17.001
Some people think
that being shy is a disease,

639
00:45:17.085 --> 00:45:19.045
but it don't bother me none.

640
00:45:19.128 --> 00:45:21.047
Don't bother me either.

641
00:45:22.382 --> 00:45:24.509
So why'd I bother bringing it up?

642
00:45:24.592 --> 00:45:26.760
'Cause I'm dumb, that's why.

643
00:45:28.012 --> 00:45:30.056
I think we make
a sharp couple of coconuts.

644
00:45:30.139 --> 00:45:32.974
I'm dumb and you're shy.
What do you think?

645
00:45:35.228 --> 00:45:38.815
I don't understand
why anybody would wanna be a fighter.

646
00:45:39.148 --> 00:45:44.445
You gotta be a moron to wanna
be a fighter, you know what I mean?

647
00:45:44.987 --> 00:45:48.489
It's a racket where you're
almost guaranteed to end up a bum.

648
00:45:48.574 --> 00:45:51.994
- I don't think you're a bum.
- I'm at least half a bum.

649
00:45:52.202 --> 00:45:54.371
But I'll tell you something.

650
00:45:55.248 --> 00:45:57.833
Worst thing about fighting
is the morning after.

651
00:45:57.916 --> 00:45:59.293
- You know?
- Morning after.

652
00:45:59.376 --> 00:46:01.253
Yeah, the morning after a fight,

653
00:46:01.335 --> 00:46:03.880
you're like a large wound,
you know what I mean?

654
00:46:03.965 --> 00:46:06.009
Sometimes I got pains all over me.

655
00:46:06.092 --> 00:46:09.804
I feel like calling a taxi to take me
from the bed into the bathroom.

656
00:46:09.887 --> 00:46:11.764
Your hair hurts, your eyes hurt.

657
00:46:11.847 --> 00:46:14.726
Your face is busted up.
Your hands are swollen.

658
00:46:14.809 --> 00:46:17.893
Look at this face. Sixty-four fights.
Look at that nose.

659
00:46:17.978 --> 00:46:20.731
You see that nose?
That nose ain't never been broken.

660
00:46:20.815 --> 00:46:23.150
I had guys busting on it.

661
00:46:23.233 --> 00:46:26.277
I had guys chewing on it,
twisting and punching it.

662
00:46:26.362 --> 00:46:27.947
I mean, whack, boom.

663
00:46:28.030 --> 00:46:30.532
These guys are hitting my nose
all the time.

664
00:46:30.614 --> 00:46:32.577
Never broke it. I'm very proud of that.

665
00:46:32.659 --> 00:46:34.244
That's rare.

666
00:46:34.329 --> 00:46:37.373
- Why do you do it if it hurts?
- Why you think?

667
00:46:38.791 --> 00:46:41.418
'Cause you can't sing and dance?

668
00:46:41.710 --> 00:46:44.213
Yeah, something like that.

669
00:46:44.297 --> 00:46:46.422
Hey, you wanna come inside?

670
00:46:48.760 --> 00:46:50.010
No, I gotta go.

671
00:46:50.094 --> 00:46:52.054
Hey, come on. I got some animals.

672
00:46:52.137 --> 00:46:54.556
I got these very rare animals inside.

673
00:46:54.639 --> 00:46:56.224
Come on in.

674
00:46:56.309 --> 00:46:57.726
No, I gotta go.

675
00:46:57.809 --> 00:47:00.646
I gotta go, too, to the bathroom. Come on.

676
00:47:01.230 --> 00:47:02.398
Come on.

677
00:47:02.481 --> 00:47:04.233
No, I gotta go.

678
00:47:04.317 --> 00:47:07.945
Look at this face.
Is that a face you could trust or what?

679
00:47:08.237 --> 00:47:12.407
Is it? They ought to stick this face
on a stamp. What do you think?

680
00:47:12.992 --> 00:47:14.577
Come on in.

681
00:47:20.166 --> 00:47:21.583
Yo, come on.

682
00:47:42.313 --> 00:47:43.523
Click.

683
00:47:49.152 --> 00:47:50.947
Yo, Adrian, you hungry?

684
00:47:51.030 --> 00:47:52.407
No.

685
00:47:52.489 --> 00:47:54.157
I got some things in there.

686
00:47:54.242 --> 00:47:57.119
If you like sodas, doughnuts or something.

687
00:47:57.286 --> 00:47:59.454
Got a couple cupcakes. Huh?

688
00:47:59.664 --> 00:48:00.748
No?

689
00:48:01.081 --> 00:48:03.626
I got some chocolate in there. No?

690
00:48:12.300 --> 00:48:14.219
Hot in here, you know?

691
00:48:16.304 --> 00:48:18.431
I could go for some music.

692
00:48:24.063 --> 00:48:25.481
Yo, Adrian.

693
00:48:25.898 --> 00:48:28.735
These are the exotic animals
I was telling you about.

694
00:48:28.818 --> 00:48:30.945
These are my friends, Cuff and Link.

695
00:48:31.027 --> 00:48:33.780
- I sold them to you.
- I know you sold them to me.

696
00:48:33.864 --> 00:48:36.367
Remember you were working
at that pet shop?

697
00:48:36.451 --> 00:48:39.911
First day you was there, and I came in
and bought both these animals?

698
00:48:39.996 --> 00:48:41.121
I remember that.

699
00:48:41.204 --> 00:48:44.916
I bought this bowl
and the animals themselves.

700
00:48:45.001 --> 00:48:47.585
Some food,
the marbles that go on the bottom there.

701
00:48:47.670 --> 00:48:49.630
Remember that mountain?

702
00:48:49.713 --> 00:48:53.885
I had to get rid of that mountain.
They kept fall over and flipping.

703
00:48:57.304 --> 00:49:00.141
Why don't you come over here
and sit down?

704
00:49:02.351 --> 00:49:04.728
It's a nice couch. I don't know.

705
00:49:06.898 --> 00:49:09.983
There's big bugs in there.
It's safer over here.

706
00:49:12.570 --> 00:49:14.322
You wanna sit down?

707
00:49:21.036 --> 00:49:22.579
These your parents?

708
00:49:22.664 --> 00:49:24.916
Yeah, that's both of them there.

709
00:49:24.998 --> 00:49:27.668
- Is this you?
- Yeah. I was eight years old.

710
00:49:27.751 --> 00:49:30.838
That's the Italian Stallion
when he was a baby.

711
00:49:33.007 --> 00:49:36.219
Come on over.
Make yourself comfortable. Relax.

712
00:49:41.681 --> 00:49:42.974
Do you have a phone?

713
00:49:43.059 --> 00:49:44.936
No, I had it pulled.

714
00:49:45.018 --> 00:49:46.853
'Cause people calling all the time,

715
00:49:46.938 --> 00:49:49.648
and who needs the aggravation, right?

716
00:49:49.731 --> 00:49:51.233
Interruptions.

717
00:49:51.608 --> 00:49:53.360
Who'd you wanna call?

718
00:49:53.443 --> 00:49:56.155
I wanna let my brother know where I am.

719
00:49:56.947 --> 00:49:58.032
Why?

720
00:49:59.701 --> 00:50:01.369
I think he might be worried.

721
00:50:01.452 --> 00:50:04.539
I'll call your brother, if that's the problem.

722
00:50:07.000 --> 00:50:09.251
Yo, Paulie! Your sister's with me!

723
00:50:09.335 --> 00:50:11.963
I'll call you back later! See you!

724
00:50:18.594 --> 00:50:20.887
You don't like the room, do you?

