if you don't wanna,

752
00:52:12.625 --> 00:52:14.460
but I wanna kiss you.

753
00:53:26.864 --> 00:53:29.911
- Heard you had a fight coming up.
- Next month.

754
00:53:29.994 --> 00:53:31.746
January 27, right?

755
00:53:31.829 --> 00:53:33.748
That's good. Come down to the gym.

756
00:53:33.831 --> 00:53:36.125
We'll get you in shape.
How's your weight?

757
00:53:36.208 --> 00:53:39.085
- 175.
- Hey, Rock. How you doing?

758
00:53:39.170 --> 00:53:41.338
Mick was looking for you up there, man.

759
00:53:41.422 --> 00:53:43.632
- For me? You're sure?
- Yeah, yeah.

760
00:53:43.715 --> 00:53:45.842
He's looking for you.
Get up there and see him.

761
00:53:45.927 --> 00:53:48.346
- He wanted me?
- Yeah. Your name's Rock, right?

762
00:53:48.429 --> 00:53:50.347
- Yeah.
- All right. Go on, babe.

763
00:54:04.652 --> 00:54:06.489
You got something for me?

764
00:54:06.572 --> 00:54:09.409
Yeah, there was some guy
from Miles Jergens looking for you.

765
00:54:09.492 --> 00:54:12.954
They need sparring partners
for Apollo Creed. There's the card.

766
00:54:13.036 --> 00:54:14.746
- When was he here?
- About an hour ago.

767
00:54:14.831 --> 00:54:18.126
They're probably looking
for sparring partners for Creed.

768
00:54:18.208 --> 00:54:20.628
I said that before, you dumb Dago!

769
00:54:22.170 --> 00:54:25.382
I been coming here for six years,
and six years you been sticking it to me.

770
00:54:25.465 --> 00:54:27.969
- How come?
- You don't wanna know!

771
00:54:28.052 --> 00:54:29.804
Yeah, I wanna know how come.

772
00:54:29.887 --> 00:54:31.931
- You wanna know?
- I wanna know now!

773
00:54:32.014 --> 00:54:34.056
Okay, I'm gonna tell you!

774
00:54:34.141 --> 00:54:38.186
You had the talent to become
a good fighter, and instead of that,

775
00:54:38.271 --> 00:54:42.400
you became a leg breaker
for some cheap, second-rate loan shark!

776
00:54:43.318 --> 00:54:44.485
It's a living.

777
00:54:44.568 --> 00:54:46.402
It's a waste of life!

778
00:55:05.005 --> 00:55:06.797
Yes. May I help you?

779
00:55:12.054 --> 00:55:14.599
Oh, you must be Mr. Rocky Balboa.

780
00:55:14.681 --> 00:55:17.518
Mr. Jergens's expecting you.
Just a moment.

781
00:55:22.690 --> 00:55:25.108
Mr. Rocky Balboa to see you, sir.

782
00:55:25.652 --> 00:55:26.777
Fine.

783
00:55:27.527 --> 00:55:30.030
- Please go in, Mr. Balboa.
- Can I have that?

784
00:55:30.114 --> 00:55:32.532
- Oh, certainly.
- Thanks.

785
00:55:37.329 --> 00:55:38.706
Mr. Balboa.

786
00:55:39.456 --> 00:55:41.250
How are you? George Jergens.

787
00:55:41.333 --> 00:55:42.960
Take a chair, please.

788
00:55:43.043 --> 00:55:44.253
Thanks.

789
00:55:46.088 --> 00:55:47.507
Mr. Balboa.

790
00:55:48.047 --> 00:55:49.925
Call me Rocky.

791
00:55:50.009 --> 00:55:52.052
Rocky, you got any representation?

792
00:55:52.135 --> 00:55:53.637
You have a manager?

793
00:55:53.721 --> 00:55:55.139
No, just me.

794
00:55:56.766 --> 00:56:00.561
Rocky, I've got a proposition
I'd like to make to you.

795
00:56:01.018 --> 00:56:04.190
- About sparring?
- Beg your pardon?

796
00:56:04.273 --> 00:56:08.735
I know you're looking for
sparring partners, and I'm very available.

797
00:56:08.945 --> 00:56:10.780
- I'm sure you are.
- Absolutely.

798
00:56:10.862 --> 00:56:12.364
Sparring with the champ
would be an honor,

799
00:56:12.447 --> 00:56:13.699
and you know what, Mr. Jergens?

800
00:56:13.782 --> 00:56:15.659
- What?
- I wouldn't take no cheap shots.

801
00:56:15.742 --> 00:56:17.911
I'd really be a good sparring partner.

802
00:56:17.996 --> 00:56:20.289
You don't understand me, Rocky.

803
00:56:20.706 --> 00:56:22.583
My proposition's this.

804
00:56:23.418 --> 00:56:25.835
Would you be interested
in fighting Apollo Creed

805
00:56:25.920 --> 00:56:28.630
for the world heavyweight championship?

806
00:56:33.219 --> 00:56:34.387
No.

807
00:56:34.469 --> 00:56:36.014
Listen, Rocky.

808
00:56:36.931 --> 00:56:38.931
Apollo's seen you fight.

809
00:56:39.766 --> 00:56:41.393
He likes you.

810
00:56:41.476 --> 00:56:43.228
He wants to fight you.

811
00:56:43.313 --> 00:56:45.106
Well, it's just that, you see,

812
00:56:45.188 --> 00:56:48.318
I fight in clubs, you know,
and I'm really a ham-and-egger.

813
00:56:48.400 --> 00:56:50.277
This guy, he's the best, and

814
00:56:50.360 --> 00:56:53.947
it wouldn't be such a good fight,
but thank you very much.

815
00:56:54.489 --> 00:56:55.907
I appreciate it.

816
00:56:55.992 --> 00:57:00.329
Rocky, do you believe that America
is the land of opportunity?

817
00:57:01.789 --> 00:57:02.873
Yeah.

818
00:57:03.708 --> 00:57:05.418
Apollo Creed does,

819
00:57:05.793 --> 00:57:07.753
and he's gonna prove it to the whole world

820
00:57:07.835 --> 00:57:10.547
by giving an unknown a shot at the title.

821
00:57:11.047 --> 00:57:13.050
And that unknown is you.

822
00:57:13.800 --> 00:57:15.635
He picked you, Rocky.

823
00:57:16.804 --> 00:57:19.097
It's the chance of a lifetime.

824
00:57:20.224 --> 00:57:22.143
You can't pass it by.

825
00:57:23.436 --> 00:57:25.063
What do you say?

826
00:57:30.943 --> 00:57:32.027
<i>All right, fellas. That's enough pictures.</i>

827
00:57:32.110 --> 00:57:33.945
<i>We wanna ask Apollo a few questions.</i>

828
00:57:34.030 --> 00:57:36.574
<i>Apollo, how do you like</i>
<i>the City of Brotherly Love?</i>

829
00:57:36.657 --> 00:57:40.077
<i>Well, just being in Philadelphia</i>
<i>makes me feel patriotic.</i>

830
00:57:40.161 --> 00:57:42.871
<i>Beautiful people in a beautiful city</i>
<i>coming up to me on the street,</i>

831
00:57:42.954 --> 00:57:44.123
<i>wishing me the best.</i>

832
00:57:44.206 --> 00:57:46.958
<i>I love my Philadelphia brothers,</i>
<i>and I'm proud to be an American.</i>

833
00:57:47.043 --> 00:57:48.585
<i>Apollo? Champ?</i>

834
00:57:48.670 --> 00:57:52.507
<i>Why did you agree to fight a man</i>
<i>who has virtually no chance of winning?</i>

835
00:57:52.590 --> 00:57:54.884
<i>If history proves one thing,</i>

836
00:57:54.967 --> 00:57:58.721
<i>American history proves that</i>
<i>everybody's got a chance to win.</i>

837
00:57:58.804 --> 00:58:01.931
<i>Didn't you guys ever hear</i>
<i>of Valley Forge or Bunker Hill?</i>

838
00:58:02.016 --> 00:58:03.518
<i>Apollo?</i>

839
00:58:03.601 --> 00:58:06.143
<i>It is a coincidence</i>
<i>that you're fighting a white man</i>

840
00:58:06.228 --> 00:58:08.188
<i>on the most celebrated day</i>
<i>in the country's history?</i>

841
00:58:08.271 --> 00:58:11.483
<i>I don't know. Is it a coincidence</i>
<i>that he's fighting a black man</i>

842
00:58:11.567 --> 00:58:13.902
<i>on the most celebrated day</i>
<i>in the country's history?</i>

843
00:58:13.987 --> 00:58:15.989
<i>- Right on, Apollo!</i>
<i>- Tell the truth, brother!</i>

844
00:58:16.072 --> 00:58:18.657
<i>Listen, Apollo.</i>
<i>How do you feel about your challenger?</i>

845
00:58:18.739 --> 00:58:21.494
<i>How do I feel about him? Come here, Rock.</i>

846
00:58:21.952 --> 00:58:23.286
<i>My main man.</i>

847
00:58:23.371 --> 00:58:26.039
<i>- Rocky, ain't you Italian?</i>
<i>- Yeah, I'm Italian.</i>

848
00:58:26.123 --> 00:58:27.833
<i>Now what does that mean?</i>

849
00:58:27.916 --> 00:58:30.795
<i>That means, if he can't fight,</i>
<i>I'll bet he can cook.</i>

850
00:58:32.505 --> 00:58:35.047
Do me a favor. His lungs, punch out.

851
00:58:35.132 --> 00:58:36.550
Paulie.

852
00:58:36.634 --> 00:58:39.846
<i>Rocky, how do you expect</i>
<i>to fight Apollo Creed?</i>

853
00:58:40.387 --> 00:58:42.639
<i>Oh, jeez, you know, Creed's the best.</i>

854
00:58:42.724 --> 00:58:44.391
<i>I guess I'll have to do the best I can.</i>

855
00:58:44.474 --> 00:58:47.143
<i>Tell me, Rocky, just between us,</i>

856
00:58:47.228 --> 00:58:50.273
<i>where did you get</i>
<i>the name "Italian Stallion"?</i>

857
00:58:50.356 --> 00:58:54.777
<i>Oh, I invented that about eight years ago</i>
<i>when I was eating dinner.</i>

858
00:58:54.860 --> 00:58:59.657
<i>Rocky, now your payday will be $150,000.</i>

859
00:58:59.782 --> 00:59:01.199
<i>Any comment?</i>

860
00:59:03.411 --> 00:59:06.331
<i>- You got no comment, Rocky, right?</i>
<i>- No.</i>

861
00:59:06.414 --> 00:59:07.873
<i>- Thank you, Rocky.</i>
<i>- Wait a minute.</i>

862
00:59:07.956 --> 00:59:10.876
<i>I just wanna say hi to my girlfriend, okay?</i>

863
00:59:10.960 --> 00:59:13.045
<i>Yo, Adrian, it's me, Rocky.</i>

864
00:59:14.172 --> 00:59:16.922
<i>You believe all this?</i>
<i>Microphones and all that stuff.</i>

865
00:59:17.007 --> 00:59:18.134
You didn't.

866
00:59:18.217 --> 00:59:20.552
<i>- Thank you, Rocky.</i>
<i>- Who you pushing, man?</i>

867
00:59:20.635 --> 00:59:22.972
<i>- Smack you in the mouth!</i>
<i>- Thank you, Rocky.</i>

868
00:59:23.056 --> 00:59:24.931
Don't it matter he making you out a fool?

869
00:59:25.016 --> 00:59:26.601
I'd break his lips.

870
00:59:26.726 --> 00:59:30.355
- He's taking cheap shots.
- Don't bother me none.

871
00:59:30.438 --> 00:59:35.275
Yo, Rocky, I guess you'll be looking
for people to help you out.

872
00:59:35.360 --> 00:59:36.652
Help what?

873
00:59:36.735 --> 00:59:37.945
You know,

874
00:59:38.027 --> 00:59:39.947
keep you living the clean life.

875
00:59:40.030 --> 00:59:42.282
I do okay, you know.

876
00:59:42.367 --> 00:59:44.327
You need someone
to help with the exercise

877
00:59:44.409 --> 00:59:48.246
and someone standing by with a towel
or running errands?

878
00:59:48.331 --> 00:59:51.083
Hey, yo, Paulie,
who cared about me yesterday? Nobody.

879
00:59:51.166 --> 00:59:53.753
So I just think I'm gonna train myself,
you know?

880
00:59:53.835 --> 00:59:56.005
Without such good people around
to help you,

881
00:59:56.088 --> 00:59:58.547
you don't have such a good chance.

882
00:59:58.675 --> 01:00:01.260
Einstein flunked out of school twice.

883
01:00:01.594 --> 01:00:02.804
That so?

884
01:00:02.969 --> 01:00:06.849
Yeah. Beethoven was deaf.
Helen Keller was blind.

885
01:00:07.431 --> 01:00:09.851
I think Rocky's got a good chance.

886
01:00:15.565 --> 01:00:17.652
Want me to get you a beer, Paulie?

887
01:00:17.735 --> 01:00:21.489
You looking to do a good deed?
Keep out of my freaking life!

888
01:00:22.407 --> 01:00:24.282
- What'd I do?
- Nothing.

889
01:00:24.367 --> 01:00:25.952
Did I say something wrong?

890
01:00:26.034 --> 01:00:27.786
You didn't say nothing. It's all right.

891
01:00:27.869 --> 01:00:29.871
That's right! You didn't say nothing!

892
01:00:29.956 --> 01:00:31.498
Nothing at all!

893
01:00:33.501 --> 01:00:34.918
I gotta go.

894
01:00:36.085 --> 01:00:38.463
Where are the freaking pretzels?

895
01:00:41.509 --> 01:00:43.469
I'd like to have a pretzel.

896
01:00:43.552 --> 01:00:45.637
Hey, we ain't got any beer?

897
01:00:46.514 --> 01:00:49.684
I thought you were supposed to
pick up some beer!

898
01:00:57.525 --> 01:01:00.152
How'd you like hearing your name
on TV tonight?

899
01:01:01.902 --> 01:01:03.405
I was shocked.

900
01:01:03.489 --> 01:01:04.907
Why'd you do that?

901
01:01:04.989 --> 01:01:06.742
You're putting me on, right?

902
01:01:06.826 --> 01:01:08.202
Absolutely.

903
01:01:08.994 --> 01:01:11.748
- What time should I expect you?
- About 7:00.

904
01:01:11.831 --> 01:01:13.750
- Okay.
- Hey.

905
01:01:31.266 --> 01:01:34.728
You know how I said
that stuff on TV didn't bother me?

906
01:01:35.146 --> 01:01:36.271
Yeah.

907
01:01:38.733 --> 01:01:40.025
It did.

908
01:01:50.661 --> 01:01:54.248
Listen, the reason I brought you here
is because

909
01:01:54.331 --> 01:01:56.668
I wanna know if you got any money
for training expenses.

910
01:01:56.751 --> 01:01:58.503
I got a few dollars.

911
01:01:58.585 --> 01:02:00.838
A few bucks? Here. Put this in your glove.

912
01:02:00.922 --> 01:02:03.965
- What's this?
- $500. Don't worry about it.

913
01:02:05.217 --> 01:02:07.135
You know, you ain't never had any luck,

914
01:02:07.219 --> 01:02:09.722
but I think this time Lady Luck
may be in your corner.

915
01:02:09.806 --> 01:02:12.724
- What do you think?
- Maybe.

916
01:02:12.809 --> 01:02:14.726
Thanks for the money, Tony.

917
01:02:14.811 --> 01:02:17.896
It's okay. Don't worry about it. I'll see you.

918
01:02:18.188 --> 01:02:19.983
- Wait a minute.
- What?

919
01:02:20.065 --> 01:02:22.193
You're in training. Come on.

920
01:02:30.326 --> 01:02:31.952
- Yo, Tony.
- What?

921
01:02:32.869 --> 01:02:35.081
You gonna show up at the fight?

922
01:02:35.164 --> 01:02:36.456
Ringside.

923
01:02:38.876 --> 01:02:40.378
I'll see you.

924
01:03:15.621 --> 01:03:16.748
Yeah.

925
01:03:22.253 --> 01:03:25.757
Hello, kid. I seen your light. Can I come in?

926
01:03:25.840 --> 01:03:28.134
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah. Good.

927
01:03:28.217 --> 01:03:30.302
Hey, it's a nice place here.

928
01:03:31.137 --> 01:03:33.931
Anyway, what I come to tell you is that,

929
01:03:35.306 --> 01:03:38.561
that what happened to you is freak luck.

930
01:03:38.643 --> 01:03:40.563
- Yeah, freak luck.
- Ain't it true?

931
01:03:40.646 --> 01:03:43.148
Look at the other guys.
They're good fighters, right?

932
01:03:43.231 --> 01:03:45.943
They're colorful. They got good records.

933
01:03:46.027 --> 01:03:48.320
They fight their guts out for peanuts.

934
01:03:48.402 --> 01:03:52.367
But you, you got a shot at the title!

935
01:03:52.449 --> 01:03:54.911
Freak luck is a strange thing, you know?

936
01:03:54.994 --> 01:03:57.496
- Sure is. Can I sit down?
- Yeah, sure.

937
01:03:59.123 --> 01:04:02.210
- What the hell are those?
- Domestic turtles.

938
01:04:02.293 --> 01:04:04.835
The one on the top is Cuff
and the other guy's Link.

939
01:04:04.920 --> 01:04:06.130
The rest are marbles.

940
01:04:06.213 --> 01:04:08.547
Yeah? They make good soup.

941
01:04:09.257 --> 01:04:10.467
Anyway.

942
01:04:10.550 --> 01:04:13.429
Look, I'm here to warn you.

943
01:04:13.512 --> 01:04:18.016
You gotta be very careful
about this shot that you got at the title.

944
01:04:18.101 --> 01:04:20.893
Because, like the Bible says,

945
01:04:20.978 --> 01:04:23.146
you ain't gonna get a second chance.

946
01:04:23.231 --> 01:04:25.358
Yeah. All right.

947
01:04:25.440 --> 01:04:27.360
You thought of that, huh?

948
01:04:27.443 --> 01:04:30.862
Well, what you need is a manager.

949
01:04:31.780 --> 01:04:33.864
A manager. Listen to me.

950
01:04:33.949 --> 01:04:37.704
I know, because I been in this racket
for 50 years.

951
01:04:37.786 --> 01:04:41.039
- 50 years, huh?
- 50 years. I've seen it all.

952
01:04:41.123 --> 01:04:44.460
- All of it. You know what I done?
- What?

953
01:04:44.543 --> 01:04:46.545
I have done it all.

954
01:04:46.628 --> 01:04:50.382
You should've seen me when I knocked
that guinea Russo out of the ring.

955
01:04:50.465 --> 01:04:52.385
Out of the goddamn ring, I tell you.

956
01:04:52.467 --> 01:04:54.512
September 14, 1923,

957
01:04:54.594 --> 01:04:58.931
and it was the same night
that Firpo knocks Dempsey out of the ring.

958
01:04:59.016 --> 01:05:01.393
So who gets the publicity? Figure that out.

959
01:05:01.476 --> 01:05:03.396
- Dempsey.
- That's right. But why?

960
01:05:03.478 --> 01:05:07.317
- 'Cause he was champ.
- No! Because he had a manager.

